==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|spenden|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|*spendan}} (attested in compounds {{m|ang|āspendan||to spend}}, {{term|forspendan||to use up, consume|lang=ang}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*spendaną}}, {{m|gem-pro|*spendōną||to spend}}, borrowed from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|expendere||to weigh out}}. Cognate with {{etyl|goh|-}} {{m|goh|spentōn||to consume, use, spend}} (whence {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|spenden||to donate, provide|lang=de}}), {{etyl|dum|-}} {{term|spenden||to spend, dedicate|lang=nl}}, Old {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|spenna||to spend|lang=is}}.

